 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=euphorion>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 9:54:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=405.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No chance?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>why would you not give that group a chance to get through? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well first of all because I knew that my wiz-friend didnt have a horse and -well let's say it nice- wasn't well equipped by any means.<br>
Knowing that I knew we were missing at least a second serious damage dealer.<br>
And I could somewhat imagine that a 60 warrior might have some trouble latest during exe fight.<br>
And last but not least simply for the fact that it was a &quot;random group&quot;. and those usually don't work out well.<br>
<br>
My guild is far away from being uber, not even close to that.<br>
We usually do it with 61/62 Pala with pretty many AAs and 61/62 cleric/Enc, me (61 Mage) and another DD (62 Beastlord with many AAs worked out best, but &quot;normal&quot; 61/62 Epic rogue works out too.) And then we add to that whoever needs to get through it.<br>
With that combination we had zero failures in about 15-20 trials.<br>
<br>
So even when the levels of the group seemed to indicate that it should be doable those &quot;random groups&quot; have one big disadvantage: missing experience together.<br>
When we do a guildgroup we know eachother and we know pretty much that everyone will do what is expected from him.<br>
we simply can rely on that the enc will mezz the &quot;right&quot; mobs, that the Pala won't switch targets once he picked one. We know that Cleric will cast the healspells at the right time and that we all will assist the MA very fast.<br>
<br>
I see groups from so called &quot;wannabe uber guilds&quot; going in with all 64/65 players and failing time after time after time.<br>
We go in with 60-62 and win every time.<br>
<br>
Those &quot;wannabe ubers&quot; raid stuff that is much harder than us. But they go there with 60-100 people. we do stuff we just can somehow do with 20-25 people. If anyone does a mistake there it more or less means a wipe. If one of those 60 or 100 does a mistake...well there are probably half a dozen of his class to replace him ;-)<br>
<br>
In my opinion the most important thing in trials is knowing eachother and knowing that you can rely on them ;-)<br>
