<br>
Finally did trial of Execution with the following:<br>
Total tries: 2<br>
<br>
Paladin<br>
Rogue<br>
Enchanter<br>
Cleric<br>
Mage<br>
Mage (me)<br>
<br>
I used Servant of Marr (lvl 62 pet spell) while the other mage used his EPIC pet. It really helped out a lot since 2 pets can help tank/kill 1 of the spawns and/or help kill the target faster.<br>
<br>
Instead of the usual AE tactic we opt to go for the single kill tactic. It was a pretty close fight.<br>
<br>
Tips:<br>
Summon a mod rod for all casters in the group. Use 1 charge of mod rod just before all wave 1 spawns are dead. Reason for this is so that you can use another charge at wave 3.<br>
<br>
Make sure everybody is ready first before you go up. All casters must be FM. Everyone should be buffed up as much as they can. (Buffs I had on were: BoA, Khuras Focusing, Xegony's Phantasmal Protection, KEI, GRM and some others that I forgot)<br>
<br>
Tank stands at the middle of the 4 benches. Casters can either stand at the north west side (opposite the npc that returns you back) or at the platform (where the boss spawns at the end of wave 4).<br>
<br>
If you have a horse, use it, it really helps a lot so you can med without getting whacked.<br>
<br>
The Boss at the end of wave 4 hits for 700 (max) but CAN be slowed. He is not too resistant so a simple MALOSINI and TASH can debuff him enough. Once slowed he is cake and can be easily tanked by a decent MA. Approximate HP: 20K<br>
<br>
If your cleric has room make sure to memorize cure disease. Once your MA is slowed by the fungal creatures cure him when possible. Nothing spells defeat more than your MA and/or other DPS melees being slowed. Some of the fungal creatures are chanter types and can cast tashania, mez, charm on you.<br>
<br>
What nukes to use? Well for me (as a mage) i used a fast cast nuke like Char which does decent damage and cast fast (about 3 sec with focus ring). Load up banishment to banish those rock creatures (they have to be malosini'd first or else they will resist). On the boss fight I use Firebolt of Tallon and Shock of Steel/Shock of Fiery Blades.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
